    <section id="page-area">
      <a id="main-content"></a>
                              <div class="tabs"></div>                          <div class="region region-content">
    <div id="block-system-main" class="block block-system">

      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="view view-homepage-items view-id-homepage_items view-display-id-front_page view-dom-id-f2a5c9c6fc9ffca9b26b0bf8902d3ec6">
        
  
  
      <div class="view-content">
          <article class="story-package-large">
      
      <h2 class="page-h1">
  
    
      <a href="http://www.cato.org/blog/injunction-against-obamas-immigration-action-policy-political-consequences">Federal Judge Stops Obama&#8217;s Executive Action on Immigration</a>
      </h2>
  

      <div class="article-meta">
  
    
      <div class="share-tools"><a href="">Share</a>
    <ul class="share-tools-list">
        <li class="twitter first"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http://www.cato.org/blog/injunction-against-obamas-immigration-action-policy-political-consequences&amp;text=Federal Judge Stops Obama&#039;s Executive Action on Immigration&amp;via=CatoInstitute&amp;related=Libertarianism" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-twitter fa-lg"></i>Tweet</a></li>
        <li class="facebook"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=http://www.cato.org/blog/injunction-against-obamas-immigration-action-policy-political-consequences" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-facebook-square fa-lg"></i>Like</a></li>
        <li class="reddit"><a href="http://reddit.com/http://www.cato.org/blog/injunction-against-obamas-immigration-action-policy-political-consequences" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-reddit fa-lg"></i>Submit</a></li>
        <li class="google last"><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http://www.cato.org/blog/injunction-against-obamas-immigration-action-policy-political-consequences" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-google-plus fa-lg"></i>Plus</a></li>
    </ul>
</div>
      </div>
  

      <div class="photo-full">
  
    
      <a href="http://www.cato.org/blog/injunction-against-obamas-immigration-action-policy-political-consequences"><picture >
<!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]-->
<source srcset="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth1000/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=etwhIpKj 1x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth1000-15x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=5YqgLrxW 1.5x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth1000-2x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=J_gDIXNG 2x" media="(min-width: 1000px)" />
<source srcset="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth800/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=drOnqKYb 1x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth800-15x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=Kwt0pGhE 1.5x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth800-2x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=6b_3nVtf 2x" media="(min-width: 800px)" />
<source srcset="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth400/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=18h9Kshg 1x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth400-15x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=0Oh5eV4V 1.5x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__minwidth400-2x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=sLurKttM 2x" media="(min-width: 400px)" />
<source srcset="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__default/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=UD73pg_l 1x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items__default-15x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=BtoELCAV 1.5x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items-right__default-2x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=9fKpP8Tv 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" />
<!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]-->
<img srcset="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items-right__default-2x/public/homepage-images/201301_immigration.jpg?itok=9fKpP8Tv 374w" alt="" title="" />
</picture></a>
      </div>
  

      <div class="text">
  
    
      <p>On Monday, a federal judge in Brownsville, Texas granted a temporary injunction to the executive action that President Obama announced in November.&nbsp; Cato scholar <a href="http://www.cato.org/people/ilya-shapiro">Ilya Shapiro</a> agrees with the ruling: “Our immigration system is broken, but it’s <a href="http://www.cato.org/blog/obamas-executive-action-good-policy-bad-law-terrible-precedent">up to Congress</a> to fix it. The president simply doesn’t get more power when Congress is gridlocked.”</p>
<ul>
<li>“<a href="http://www.cato.org/blog/federal-judge-stops-obamas-executive-action-immigration">Federal Judge Stops Obama’s Executive Action on Immigration</a>,” by Ilya Shapiro</li>
<li>“<a href="http://www.cato.org/blog/injunction-against-obamas-immigration-action-policy-political-consequences">Injunction against Obama’s Immigration Action: Policy and Political Consequences</a>,” by Alex Nowrasteh</li>
</ul>

      </div>
  
    </article>
      <article class="story-package-large">
      
      <h2 class="page-h1">
  
    
      <a href="http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind"><em>The Libertarian Mind: A Manifesto for Freedom</em></a>
      </h2>
  

      <div class="article-meta">
  
    
      <div class="share-tools"><a href="">Share</a>
    <ul class="share-tools-list">
        <li class="twitter first"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind&amp;text=&lt;em&gt;The Libertarian Mind: A Manifesto for Freedom&lt;/em&gt;&amp;via=CatoInstitute&amp;related=Libertarianism" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-twitter fa-lg"></i>Tweet</a></li>
        <li class="facebook"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-facebook-square fa-lg"></i>Like</a></li>
        <li class="reddit"><a href="http://reddit.com/http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-reddit fa-lg"></i>Submit</a></li>
        <li class="google last"><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-google-plus fa-lg"></i>Plus</a></li>
    </ul>
</div>
      </div>
  

      <div class="photo-thumb">
  
    
      <a href="http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind"><picture >
<!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]-->
<source srcset="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items-right__default/public/right-homepage-images/libertarianmindstore1.jpg?itok=zTq3jaxP 1x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items-right__default-15x/public/right-homepage-images/libertarianmindstore1.jpg?itok=PKRb91KQ 1.5x, http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items-right__default-2x/public/right-homepage-images/libertarianmindstore1.jpg?itok=F3t5HCDL 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" />
<!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]-->
<img srcset="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/styles/resp__img__homepage-items-right__default-2x/public/right-homepage-images/libertarianmindstore1.jpg?itok=F3t5HCDL 374w" alt="" title="" />
</picture></a>
      </div>
  

      <div class="text">
  
    
      <p>Two long wars, chronic deficits, the financial crisis, the costly drug war, the growth of executive power under Presidents Bush and Obama, and the revelations about NSA abuses, have given rise to a growing libertarian movement in our country – with a greater focus on individual liberty and less government power. <a href="http://www.cato.org/people/david-boaz">David Boaz</a>’s newly released <a href="http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind"><em>The Libertarian Mind</em></a> is a comprehensive guide to the history, philosophy, and growth of the&nbsp;libertarian movement, with incisive analyses of today’s most pressing issues and policies. <em>The Libertarian Mind</em> is the ultimate resource for the current, burgeoning libertarian movement.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cato.org/libertarianmind"><em>The Libertarian Mind: A Manifesto for Freedom</em></a></li>
</ul>

      </div>
  
    </article>
      <article class="story-package-large">
      
      <h2 class="page-h1">
  
    
      <a href="http://www.cato.org/publications/research-briefs-economic-policy/how-are-small-banks-faring-under-dodd-frank">How Are Small Banks Faring under Dodd-Frank?</a>
      </h2>
  

      <div class="article-meta">
  
    
      <div class="share-tools"><a href="">Share</a>
    <ul class="share-tools-list">
        <li class="twitter first"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http://www.cato.org/publications/research-briefs-economic-policy/how-are-small-banks-faring-under-dodd-frank&amp;text=How Are Small Banks Faring under Dodd-Frank?&amp;via=CatoInstitute&amp;related=Libertarianism" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-twitter fa-lg"></i>Tweet</a></li>
        <li class="facebook"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=http://www.cato.org/publications/research-briefs-economic-policy/how-are-small-banks-faring-under-dodd-frank" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-facebook-square fa-lg"></i>Like</a></li>
        <li class="reddit"><a href="http://reddit.com/http://www.cato.org/publications/research-briefs-economic-policy/how-are-small-banks-faring-under-dodd-frank" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-reddit fa-lg"></i>Submit</a></li>
        <li class="google last"><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http://www.cato.org/publications/research-briefs-economic-policy/how-are-small-banks-faring-under-dodd-frank" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-google-plus fa-lg"></i>Plus</a></li>
    </ul>
</div>
      </div>
  

      <div class="text">
  
    
      <p>Although new regulations associated with&nbsp;the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act affect many types of financial institutions and other companies, the effect on small banks has emerged as a matter of considerable concern.&nbsp; <a href="http://www.cato.org/publications/research-briefs-economic-policy/how-are-small-banks-faring-under-dodd-frank">New research</a> from Hester Peirce, Ian Robinson, and Thomas Stratmann describes and analyzes the results of a 2013 survey of approximately 200 small banks. The authors’ findings suggest that a large majority of small banks view Dodd-Frank as extremely burdensome, and many banks have reconsidered their product and service offerings in response.</p>
<ul>
<li>“<a href="http://www.cato.org/publications/research-briefs-economic-policy/how-are-small-banks-faring-under-dodd-frank">How Are Small Banks Faring under Dodd-Frank?</a>,” by Hester Peirce, Ian Robinson, and Thomas Stratmann</li>
</ul>

      </div>
  
    </article>
      <article class="story-package-large">
      
      <h2 class="page-h1">
  
    
      <a href="http://www.cato.org/cato-journal/winter-2015">New <em>Cato Journal</em> Tackles Political Capitalism, China‘s Transition to a Liberal Society</a>
      </h2>
  

      <div class="article-meta">
  
    
      <div class="share-tools"><a href="">Share</a>
    <ul class="share-tools-list">
        <li class="twitter first"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http://www.cato.org/cato-journal/winter-2015&amp;text=New &lt;em&gt;Cato Journal&lt;/em&gt; Tackles Political Capitalism, China‘s Transition to a Liberal Society&amp;via=CatoInstitute&amp;related=Libertarianism" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-twitter fa-lg"></i>Tweet</a></li>
        <li class="facebook"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=http://www.cato.org/cato-journal/winter-2015" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-facebook-square fa-lg"></i>Like</a></li>
        <li class="reddit"><a href="http://reddit.com/http://www.cato.org/cato-journal/winter-2015" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-reddit fa-lg"></i>Submit</a></li>
        <li class="google last"><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http://www.cato.org/cato-journal/winter-2015" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-fw fa-google-plus fa-lg"></i>Plus</a></li>
    </ul>
</div>
      </div>
  

      <div class="text">
  
    
      <p>Political capitalism is an economic and political system in which the economic and political elite cooperate for their mutual benefit.&nbsp; In <a href="http://www.cato.org/cato-journal/winter-2015">the new issue of <em>Cato Journal</em></a>, Randall G. Holcombe contends that we should understand <a href="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/serials/files/cato-journal/2015/2/cj-v35n1-2.pdf">political capitalism as a distinct economic system</a>, as opposed to an intermediate system lying between capitalism and socialism.&nbsp; Also in this issue, Weiying Zhang analyzes the role that <a href="http://object.cato.org/sites/cato.org/files/serials/files/cato-journal/2015/2/cj-v35n1-1.pdf">ideas and leadership</a> play in China’s economic and political transition to a liberal society.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cato.org/cato-journal/winter-2015">Winter 2015 Issue of <em>Cato Journal</em></a></li>
</ul>

      </div>
  
    </article>
      </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
</div>  </div>
</div>
